SH.DYN.NCOM.FE.ZS-gt.def: Mortality from CVD, cancer, diabetes or CRD is the percent of 30-year-old-people who would die before their 70th birthday from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes,  or chronic respiratory disease, assuming that s/he would experience current mortality rates at every age and s/he would not die from any other cause of death (e.g., injuries or HIV/AIDS).
SH.DYN.NCOM.FE.ZS-gt.name: Mortality from CVD, cancer, diabetes or CRD between exact ages 30 and 70
SH.DYN.NCOM.FE.ZS-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.DYN.NCOM.MA.ZS-gt.def: Mortality from CVD, cancer, diabetes or CRD is the percent of 30-year-old-people who would die before their 70th birthday from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes,  or chronic respiratory disease, assuming that s/he would experience current mortality rates at every age and s/he would not die from any other cause of death (e.g., injuries or HIV/AIDS).
SH.DYN.NCOM.MA.ZS-gt.name: Mortality from CVD, cancer, diabetes or CRD between exact ages 30 and 70
SH.DYN.NCOM.MA.ZS-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.DYN.NCOM.ZS-gt.def: Mortality from CVD, cancer, diabetes or CRD is the percent of 30-year-old-people who would die before their 70th birthday from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes,  or chronic respiratory disease, assuming that s/he would experience current mortality rates at every age and s/he would not die from any other cause of death (e.g., injuries or HIV/AIDS).

SH.DYN.NMRT-gt.def: Neonatal mortality rate is the number of neonates dying before reaching 28 days of age, per 1,000 live births in a given year.

SH.DYN.NMRT-gt.source: Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.

SH.STA.AIRP.FE.P5-gt.def: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution is the number of deaths attributable to the joint effects of household and ambient air pollution in a year per 100,000 population. The rates are age-standardized.  Following diseases are taken into account: acute respiratory infections (estimated for all ages); cerebrovascular diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); ischaemic heart diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in adults (estimated above 25 years); and lung cancer in adults (estimated above 25 years).
SH.STA.AIRP.FE.P5-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution, age-standardized
SH.STA.AIRP.FE.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.AIRP.MA.P5-gt.def: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution is the number of deaths attributable to the joint effects of household and ambient air pollution in a year per 100,000 population. The rates are age-standardized.  Following diseases are taken into account: acute respiratory infections (estimated for all ages); cerebrovascular diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); ischaemic heart diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in adults (estimated above 25 years); and lung cancer in adults (estimated above 25 years).
SH.STA.AIRP.MA.P5-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution, age-standardized
SH.STA.AIRP.MA.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.AIRP.P5-gt.def: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution is the number of deaths attributable to the joint effects of household and ambient air pollution in a year per 100,000 population. The rates are age-standardized.  Following diseases are taken into account: acute respiratory infections (estimated for all ages); cerebrovascular diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); ischaemic heart diseases in adults (estimated above 25 years); chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in adults (estimated above 25 years); and lung cancer in adults (estimated above 25 years).
SH.STA.AIRP.P5-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution, age-standardized

SH.STA.POIS.P5-gt.def:
Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisonings is the number of deaths from unintentional poisonings in a year per 100,000 population.  Unintentional poisoning can
be caused by household chemicals, pesticides, kerosene, carbon monoxide and medicines, or can be the result of environmental contamination or occupational chemical exposure.
SH.STA.POIS.P5-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning
SH.STA.POIS.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE-gt.def: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisonings is the number of female deaths from unintentional poisonings in a year per 100,000 female population.  Unintentional poisoning can be caused by household chemicals, pesticides, kerosene, carbon monoxide and medicines, or can be the result of environmental contamination or occupational chemical exposure.
SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning
SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.POIS.P5.MA-gt.def:
Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisonings is the number of male deaths from unintentional poisonings in a year per 100,000 male population. Unintentional poisoning can
be caused by household chemicals, pesticides, kerosene, carbon monoxide and medicines, or can be the result of environmental contamination or occupational chemical exposure.
SH.STA.POIS.P5.MA-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning
SH.STA.POIS.P5.MA-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.SUIC.FE.P5-gt.def: Suicide mortality rate is the number of suicide deaths in a year per 100,000 population. Crude suicide rate (not age-adjusted).
SH.STA.SUIC.FE.P5-gt.name: Suicide mortality rate
SH.STA.SUIC.FE.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.SUIC.MA.P5-gt.def: Suicide mortality rate is the number of suicide deaths in a year per 100,000 population. Crude suicide rate (not age-adjusted).
SH.STA.SUIC.MA.P5-gt.name: Suicide mortality rate
SH.STA.SUIC.MA.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.SUIC.P5-gt.def: Suicide mortality rate is the number of suicide deaths in a year per 100,000 population. Crude suicide rate (not age-adjusted).
SH.STA.SUIC.P5-gt.name: Suicide mortality rate
SH.STA.SUIC.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.TRAF.P5-gt.def: Mortality caused by road traffic injury is estimated road traffic fatal injury deaths per 100,000 population.
SH.STA.TRAF.P5-gt.name: Mortality caused by road traffic injury
SH.STA.TRAF.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).

SH.STA.WASH.P5-gt.def: Mortality rate attributed to unsafe water, unsafe sanitation and lack of hygiene is deaths attributable to unsafe water, sanitation and hygiene focusing on inadequate WASH services per 100,000 population. Death rates are calculated by dividing the number of deaths by the total population. In this estimate, only the impact of diarrhoeal diseases, intestinal nematode infections, and protein-energy malnutrition are taken into account.
SH.STA.WASH.P5-gt.name: Mortality rate attributed to unsafe water, unsafe sanitation and lack of hygiene
SH.STA.WASH.P5-gt.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).
